//axhob_operation
{mkr_bottle_cleanup}

NOTE: This sequence within
{opbs_bottle_start}
removes any previous container instance to ensure a clean state before launching a new
{at_bottle_container}.

//axhos_step
. *Query Container Existence*:
.. {rbbc_call}
podman container exists for
{at_bottle_container_name}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«CONTAINER_EXISTS»` as result

//axhos_step
. *Remove Previous Container* (conditional):
.. If `«CONTAINER_EXISTS»` is true:
... {rbbc_call}
podman stop with 5-second timeout for
{at_bottle_container_name}
... {rbbc_call}
podman rm --force for
{at_bottle_container_name}
if still present after timeout
... {rbbc_call}
podman container exists to verify removal
... {rbbc_require}
container completely removed from runtime

//axhob_operation
{mkr_bottle_launch}

NOTE: This sequence within
{opbs_bottle_start}
instantiates and configures the service container for the
{at_bottle_service}.

//axhos_step
. *Launch
{at_bottle_container}*:
.. {rbbc_call}
podman run with:
... image:
{rbrn_bottle_vessel}:{rbrn_bottle_consecration}
... name:
{at_bottle_container_name}
... network: exclusive attachment to
{at_enclave_network}
... volumes: apply
{rbrn_volume_mounts}
specifications
... restart policy: unless-stopped
.. {rbbc_require}
container launched successfully

//axhos_step
. *Verify Network Configuration*:
.. Allow container initialization with podman's default network configuration
.. {rbbc_call}
{mkc_interface_check}
to verify container network interface is active
.. {rbbc_require}
network interface ready for operation

//axhob_operation
{mkr_bottle_create}

NOTE: This sequence within
{opbr_bottle_run}
creates a transient
{at_bottle_container}
from the configured image, establishing network connectivity and volume mounts without persisting the container after execution.

//axhos_step
. *Configure Container Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_use}
{rbrn_bottle_vessel}:{rbrn_bottle_consecration} as source image
.. {rbbc_use}
{at_enclave_network} for exclusive network attachment
.. {rbbc_use}
{at_sentry_container} address as DNS resolver
.. {rbbc_use}
{rbrn_volume_mounts} specifications for filesystem access

//axhos_step
. *Create Container*:
.. {rbbc_call}
podman create with:
... Image: {rbrn_bottle_vessel}:{rbrn_bottle_consecration}
... Network: {at_enclave_network} (exclusive)
... DNS: {at_sentry_container} address
... Volumes: {rbrn_volume_mounts}
... Cleanup flag: `--rm` (automatic removal on exit)
.. Allow podman to assign unique container name
.. {rbbc_require}
container created successfully
.. {rbbc_store}
`«CONTAINER_ID»` from creation response

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution creates a configured transient container ready for command execution.

//axhob_operation
{mkr_command_exec}

NOTE: This sequence within
{opbr_bottle_run}
executes a specified command within the
{at_bottle_container},
running the operation in the configured container environment.

//axhos_step
. *Execute Command*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«CONTAINER_ID»` available from container creation
.. {rbbc_require}
`«COMMAND_ARGS»` provided as command specification
.. {rbbc_call}
podman exec for `«CONTAINER_ID»` with `«COMMAND_ARGS»`
.. {rbbc_require}
command execution completes

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution runs the requested command within the container, with output returned to caller.

